	<fdd:localUse>
		<fdd:experience>The Library of Congress has a small amount of Windows Media Audio files in its collections.</fdd:experience>
		<fdd:preference>See the Library of Congress Recommended Formats Statement for format preferences for <a href="https://www.loc.gov/preservation/resources/rfs/audio.html">audio works</a>.
		</fdd:preference>
	</fdd:localUse>
	<fdd:sustainabilityFactors>
		<fdd:disclosure>Microsoft's proprietary <fddLink id="fdd000067">ASF</fddLink> wrapper format is fully documented. For information about the disclosure of information about the bitstreams wrapped by WMA, see the descriptions of individual codecs listed under <i>Relationships</i>, above.
		</fdd:disclosure>
		<fdd:documentation>For wrapper documentation, see <fddLink id="fdd000067">ASF</fddLink>. See also citations in <a href="#useful">Useful references</a> below.
		</fdd:documentation>
		<fdd:adoption>Widely adopted.
		</fdd:adoption>
		<fdd:licensingAndPatents>See <fddLink id="fdd000067">ASF</fddLink>.
		</fdd:licensingAndPatents>
		<fdd:transparency>See information on versions that incorporate different codecs: <fddLink id="fdd000097">WMA_WMA9</fddLink>, <fddLink id="fdd000098">WMA_WMA9_PRO</fddLink>, and <fddLink id="fdd000099">WMA_WMA9_LL</fddLink>.
		</fdd:transparency>
		<fdd:selfDocumentation>See <fddLink id="fdd000067">ASF</fddLink>
		</fdd:selfDocumentation>
		<fdd:externalDependencies>None
		</fdd:externalDependencies>
		<fdd:techProtection>See <fddLink id="fdd000067">ASF</fddLink>
		</fdd:techProtection>
	</fdd:sustainabilityFactors>
	<fdd:qualityAndFunctionalityFactors>
		<fdd:soundQF>
			<fdd:normalSound>Good support.</fdd:normalSound>
			<fdd:fidelity>Moderate to excellent; outcome will depend on codec selected and upon the type and level of compression.</fdd:fidelity>
			<fdd:channels>Supported in <fddLink id="fdd000098">WMA_WMA9_PRO</fddLink>
			</fdd:channels>
			<fdd:samples>Appears to be some support for <fddLink id="fdd000102">MIDI_SD</fddLink>; not investigated at this writing.</fdd:samples>
			<fdd:beyondSound>Support for various elements offered by <fddLink id="fdd000067">ASF</fddLink>.</fdd:beyondSound>
		</fdd:soundQF>
	</fdd:qualityAndFunctionalityFactors>
